                     <interp inst="t18220522-76-person723" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's, on the second floor; the prisoner lodged in the same room. I had received 3 l. from my Captain. On the 18th of May, while I was at the docks, my property was stolen; I saw him lock the room up before I went out. I returned at eight o'clock at night, and the landlord gave me information. He had lodged there a fortnight, and did not say he was going to leave.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220522-76-person724">
                  JAMES 
                  COTLMAN
               <interp inst="t18220522-76-person724" type="surname" value="COTLMAN"></interp>
