                  </persName>
            . I am an officer of Poplar. The prisoner was stopped and given into my charge, and a bag of clothes was produced at the watch-house, which Jacobs claimed.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220522-76-person725">
                  THOMAS 
                  PITT
               <interp inst="t18220522-76-person725" type="surname" value="PITT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220522-76-person725" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220522-76-person725" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman of Poplar. I stopped the prisoner on the 18th of May, at 11 o'clock at night, with a bag of clothes; he said he came from London Bridge, and was going on board his ship; I let him pass but kept the clothes; and next night I saw him again and took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220522-76-person726">
